Careers with Impact

More than one million Australians trust HESTA with their money. HESTA is a top-performing industry super fund working for real-world impact. We use our expertise and influence to deliver strong long-term returns while accelerating our contribution to a more sustainable world.

HESTA is also an inspiring and rewarding place to work. That's because what we do makes a difference to the lives of our members. People who provide some of the best health, education and community services in the world are HESTA members - and we are proud to serve them.





Bring your authentic and passionate self to this exceptional role #careerswithimpact

As an Investment Analyst - Systematic Research, you'll play a meaningful role in supporting dynamic asset allocation through quantitative research and market analysis. Working closely with senior investment leaders, you'll contribute to the development and refinement of systematic models, signals and portfolio construction approaches used to assess valuations, risks and opportunities across asset classes.

You'll be involved in end-to-end investment research, analysing market and economic developments, testing ideas, and engaging with internal stakeholders and external research partners to challenge thinking and strengthen outcomes. Your work will directly inform investment insights and recommendations.

A day in the role may include:

Analysing market data and macro signals to support asset allocation decisions
Contributing to the development, testing and documentation of quantitative models and investment signals
Collaborating with portfolio managers and investment colleagues on market scenarios and research insights
Preparing clear analysis and recommendations to support investment discussions
Engaging with external managers, banks or research partners to explore ideas and market views

This role suits an analytically minded investment professional with a few years' experience who enjoys combining data, markets and technology, and is looking to deepen their impact within a collaborative, high-performing investment team.

Benefits that matter and make a difference for our employees

Leave for those moments that matter, an additional 6 days of leave at the end of year, up to 6 days paid volunteer leave, gender neutral paid parental leave of 20 weeks, Gender Affirmation leave, reproductive health and wellbeing leave, Cultural and Ceremonial leave. Access your LSL after 3 years, take AL at half pay, and purchase up to 2 weeks additional leave (just to name a few!).
Your Professional development matters, up to $5k per year professional development and up to 8 days professional development leave, HESTA scholarships and free access to a range of premium learning tools.
Your health and wellbeing matters, free annual flu shots and skin checks, incredible social events throughout the year and a comprehensive employee assistance program available 24/7.
Your financial wellbeing matters, up to 15% super, financial planning support, end of year payment for all Enterprise Agreement-covered employees, incentivised Employee Referral Program and novated lease options.

We celebrate, value and include people of all backgrounds, genders, identities, cultures and abilities. Job Title: Senior Business Analyst | Finance ERP Implementation
Ad Text:

Robert Half is partnering with a leading organisation undergoing significant growth and transformation. They are seeking a high-calibre Finance Process & Automation Business Analyst to optimise how the business leverages of a ERP and deliver meaningful process efficiencies across Finance.

6 + 6-month contract
Immediate start
Opportunity to make a significant impact during a period of growth and transformation
Work within a collaborative and supportive environment

At WorkCover Queensland, our vision is to be the best workers’ compensation insurer. To make a positive difference in people’s lives and keep Queenslanders working. We are committed to delivering outstanding outcomes through a high-performance culture, where strong leadership, innovation, and collaboration are at the heart of everything we do.  

Our organisation is driven by purpose and integrity, working together as One Team. We value diversity of thought and experience, and welcome those who bring authenticity, strategic thinking, and strong leadership to their work. If you're a senior leader who thrives on building capability, enabling performance, and driving transformation, you'll find purpose and impact here at WorkCover.  

About the Opportunity: 

WorkCover has entered an exciting new chapter, driven by our 2030 Strategy and strong executive leadership. Reporting to the Head of Transformation Delivery and part of the leadership team, the newly created Senior Manager, Business Analysis will play a pivotal role in enabling enterprise-wide transformation and delivering meaningful outcomes for our people, customers, and the broader community. 

Lead transformation with vision and impact! In this role, you’ll shape the future of how WorkCover delivers change. You’ll align strategy with execution, partnering with senior leaders across Digital, Operations, and Transformation to drive outcomes that matter. Leading a high-performing Business Analysis team, you’ll champion enterprise frameworks, embed best practice, and inspire consistency that accelerates success. Your leadership will influence the organisation’s transformation journey and set a benchmark for excellence across the industry. 

In this role, you’ll make an impact by: 

Leading teams and outcomes: Provide strategic leadership of the Business Analysis function as a strategic enabler of organisational transformation,  
Driving excellence: Establish governance and quality standards, uplift frameworks and methodologies, and ensure consistency of practice to enable successful outcomes. 
Coaching and mentoring: Develop capability across the Business Analysis function through targeted training, mentoring, and building communities of practice that foster performance and impact. 
Partnering across the business: Act as a trusted advisor to leaders and teams, aligning Business Analysis with organisational strategy and influencing priorities through insights and expertise. 
Owning the big picture: Provide strategic leadership of the Business Analysis Practice, ensuring alignment of capability, methodology, and delivery with organisational priorities, transformation initiatives and regulatory requirements 

It’s a diverse, influential role - perfect for a collaborative and outcomes-focused operational leader who thrives in complexity, brings people together and drives purposeful transformation that delivers meaningful outcomes.  

A bit about you:  

Significant proven experience leading large, complex Business Analysis practices, including strategic planning, capability development, and team growth (5+ Years). 
Extensive Business Analysis expertise across business, operations and technology, and organisational contexts, with a strong record in enterprise transformation and large-scale change delivery (10+ Years). 
Demonstrated success in maturing Business Analysis practices through frameworks, methodologies, governance structures, and quality assurance processes. 
Strong knowledge of contemporary delivery approaches (Agile, SAFe, hybrid) and their application in enterprise environments. 
Ability to influence senior and executive stakeholders, providing evidence-based insights that shape strategy, priorities, and investment decisions. 
Experience managing vendors and partners to optimise capability and support transformation priorities, with deep understanding of financial services, insurance, and regulatory environments. 
Tertiary qualifications in Business, IT, or a related discipline; post-graduate credentials in management, strategy, or leadership highly regarded. 

A bit about us :

The Transformation Delivery team sits within our Operations and Technology and is passionate about delivering impactful change for the organisation and Queenslanders. We support each other professionally and personally - whether deep in delivery, on a lunch break walk, or sharing travel stories. We celebrate our wins, recognise achievements, and foster a culture of support, shared success, and continuous improvement.    

Working in a collaborative team environment within a supportive and engaged organisation, you’ll enjoy hybrid working, access to personalised learning and development opportunities and the holistic support of our health and wellbeing program. We offer industry competitive salaries, a generous superannuation scheme (including co-contribution) and study assistance. You can find out more about our Employee Benefits by visiting Working at WorkCover Qld.  

How do I apply?  

Please submit your resume and a covering letter of no more than two pages, outlining your suitability for the role including your leadership experience, strategic and operational achievements, your motivations, and alignment with our values and vision.   

Applications close at 5pm, Tuesday 27 January 2026. 

We are committed to ensuring WorkCover reflects the diversity of the Queensland community. We welcome applications from First Nations peoples, members of the LGBTQIA+SB community, people of all ages, people who are neurodivergent, people with disability, and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.  

To provide you the best experience, we can support with accommodations or adjustments at any stage of the recruitment process. Simply inform our recruitment team during your conversation with them.  

Pre-employment checks will be conducted on all prospective employees. This will include a Right to Work in Australia Check, Police Check, Education Check, Reference Check and where appropriate a Visa Check. The information provided will be treated as confidential in accordance with the Information Privacy Act 2009 (Qld).  

Please note: WorkCover does not accept unsolicited resumes from agencies and will not be liable for related fees. All recruitment is managed internally. Agencies must not represent or promote WorkCover roles without prior written authorisation.

A values-driven not-for-profit organisation is seeking an experienced Manager, Data Strategy & Governance to lead its transformation into a truly data-centric organisation. This is a rare opportunity to shape how data is governed, trusted, and leveraged to deliver meaningful insights that support strategic objectives and long-term impact.

Reporting into senior leadership, you will define and execute a multi-year data strategy and governance framework, ensuring data is treated as a strategic asset and positioned to support AI adoption, advanced analytics, and data-driven decision making.

The Opportunity

In this pivotal role, you will lead the establishment of strong data foundations across the organisation, balancing innovation with privacy, security, and regulatory compliance. You will drive a clear roadmap that elevates data literacy, improves insight maturity, and enables Data as a Product (DaaP) thinking across the business.

Key Responsibilities

Develop and implement a comprehensive data strategy and governance framework, including policies, standards, and procedures.

Establish and embed data governance structures defining data ownership, stewardship, and accountability.

Lead delivery of a multi-year data and analytics roadmap, supporting AI readiness from 2026 onwards.

Champion AI readiness and Data as a Product, ensuring high-quality, well-governed data assets.

Lead and develop onshore and offshore data analytics and BI teams, providing mentoring and performance leadership.

Design and implement scalable data architecture, data models, taxonomies, and metadata repositories.

Oversee the implementation of business intelligence and analytics platforms, delivering actionable insights.

Partner with business leaders to identify data and analytics opportunities aligned to strategic goals.

Establish robust data quality management processes.

Work closely with Information Security to ensure strong data privacy, security, and regulatory compliance.

Deliver data literacy initiatives to uplift organisational capability.

Manage vendor, MSP, and technology partner relationships.

Drive innovation through advanced analytics, including predictive analytics and machine learning where appropriate.

About You

You are a strategic and hands-on data leader who thrives in purpose-led environments. You balance governance with enablement and can translate complex data concepts into clear, practical outcomes for non-technical stakeholders.

Essential Experience & Skills

5+ years’ experience in data management, analytics, or data governance roles.

Proven experience defining and implementing enterprise data strategies, including support for AI initiatives.

Strong knowledge of data governance frameworks and best practices.

Experience implementing and managing BI and analytics platforms.

Solid understanding of data architecture, data modelling, and metadata management.

Knowledge of data privacy, security, and regulatory compliance.

Demonstrated people leadership experience across technical teams.

Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills.

Strong analytical and problem-solving capability with high attention to detail.

Desirable Experience

Hands-on experience with Power BI, Tableau, or similar visualisation tools.

Experience preparing and optimising datasets for AI and machine learning initiatives.

Knowledge of data integration, ETL tools, and processes.

Exposure to predictive analytics and advanced analytics techniques.

Experience with data quality tools and methodologies.

Background in healthcare or education data environments.

Why Apply?

Influence enterprise-level data strategy in a mission-driven not-for-profit.

Lead an organisation through AI readiness and data maturity uplift.

High-impact role with executive visibility.

Collaborative, values-led culture with long-term vision.

Deep understanding of identity management, network security, and access models.
Core Skills:

Exceptional stakeholder management skills with the ability to influence at all levels.
Expertise in creating high-quality artefacts: Traceability matrices, process flows, and risk registers.
Ability to work autonomously within a fast-paced, regulated environment.
Certifications: CBAP, Agile BA, SAFe, or ITIL (Highly Regarded).

ImPACt Distribution Centre, Ravenhall, VIC 

Become a Part of the Team 


Nike Pacific fosters growth, creativity, and diversity, welcoming achievers and visionaries to a dynamic logistics team at the ImPACt Distribution Centre. Join us to drive innovation and deliver inspiration through omnichannel operations. 

This role is essential to Nike Pacific’s distribution strategy, ensuring operations are precise, agile, and collaborative. Be part of a team committed to excellence and innovation every day. 

Team Overview 


Pacific’s Logistics Operations Team delivers tailored supply chain services to all Nike internal and external customers. WHO YOU’LL WORK WITH

Working knowledge of 3PL distribution within Australia and New Zealand, with an ability to work across a matrix environment.

Strong stakeholder engagement and influencing skills. 

Proficiency in SAP, WMS, TMS, advanced Microsoft Office.  

Strong analytical skills including cost modelling, performance management, and financial review.

Lead & inspire to deliver the Pacific Logistics Purpose, growing revenue through precision delivery of Nike product to fulfill marketplace demand when, where and how it actualizes.

Manage & influence multiple Logistics Partner Operational relationships to drive process excellence and continuous improvements to enhance the consumer experience, service, convenience, cost and sustainability.

Own and deliver Logistics Performance results within clearly defined Nike Operational and Marketplace KPI’s in partnership with our Logistics partners.

Lead, Coach, Drive, and Inspire.

Build Logistics operational knowledge and experience, ensuring service excellence and end to end efficiencies (including Returns).

Drive high engagement, provide opportunities for growth and visibility, and develop customer and consumer centric mindsets.

Responsible for logistics’ input into cross-functional, Geographies (GEO) and Global forums such as Integrated Fulfillment Planning, Marketplace Supply Chain, Finance, Inventory Ops and Global Supply Chain Operations forums.

Accountable for and ensuring the knowledge and application of company policies & procedures across logistics ensuring compliance. Drive internal & external audits of these controls.

Responsible for the partnership mindset, investment, and development of the relationship with Nike Logistics partners.

Leverage data & insights to drive continuous improvements and inform decision prioritization and trade-offs across the logistics operations.

Identify and recommend strategic initiatives internally and with Logistics Partners to co-develop Pacifica Logistics and Supply Chain Strategies.

Job Title: Director, Multiple Opportunities - Data Governance, Data Strategy and Delivery
Company: Australian Transaction Reports and Analysis Centre (AUSTRAC)
Category:
Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
AUSTRAC is hiring two positions to join the Data Strategy and Collections branch, where our focus is strengthening the agency's enterprise data governance strategy, and maximising the value of our data in achieving regulatory and intelligence priorities This recruitment process will be used to fill current vacancies and build a merit pool for future roles. 

These Director roles offer a unique opportunity to help shape major enterprise shifts and uplift data culture and literacy across AUSTRAC. As a key data leader of the Data Division, your specialist data expertise and oversight across data capability initiatives will cultivate AUSTRAC's data governance strategy and culture. 

Be part of our transformation journey as we evolve into a world leading data-driven, digital agency in financial regulation and intelligence. If you embrace challenges diligently, are passionate about leading teams in a collaborative environment, and are eager to make a meaningful impact we encourage you to apply. 

Director, Data Strategy and Delivery 

You will be responsible for the coordination, alignment and delivery of AUSTRAC's strategic data capability initiatives to support data integrity, continuous enhancement and seamless integration. Your role is critical in ensuring high-quality, consistent data is available within AUSTRAC's regulatory and intelligence functions. You will influence and guide various stakeholders in integrating data outcomes in portfolio projects, while instilling best practice data governance and management principles. As a decisive and people-focussed leader, you will nurture a high-performing team of data professionals to deliver high-quality, operational data capabilities which are critical to support AUSTRAC's regulatory and intelligence operations. 

Key duties include: 

Design, develop and maintain AUSTRAC’s data initiatives and plans to ensure accurate and consistent data is available for AUSTRAC’s regulatory and intelligence functions. 
Product management of strategic data initiatives to align with AUSTRAC’s Reform and Transformation priorities, ensuring effective risk managemnet, governance pracices and sustainability. 
Lead cross-functional teams to design and deliver data plans and other strategic initiatives within cloud-based data integration architectures—including ETL and streaming processes, APIs, and data warehouse systems, and facilitate the democratisation and sharing of data with internal and external partners. 
Collaborate with various stakeholders to elicit business needs and design strategic data solutions that enable their use in analysis, business intelligence, and data science; overseeing the translation of these into data plans, projects, and initiatives. 

Director, Data Governance 

Your focus will be establishing and ensuring adherence to AUSTRAC's data governance frameworks, with the goal of optimising the use and flow of data whilst ensuring our data is safe and secure. Your role will be pivotal in managing controls to drive actionable data for intelligence, regulatory operations, and corporate needs. You will serve as a point of escalation for governance, data quality and protection issues and will work closely with agency leadership to improve the quality and value of core data assets. As a trusted, governance leader, you will build agency-wide understanding of data governance and lead a high-performing team to embed these practices across the agency.  

Key duties include:  

Lead the design, implementation and continuous improvement of AUSTRAC’s enterprise data governance framework, including AI governance and assurance activities, ensuring alignment with whole-of-government requirements and responsible use of AI and automated systems. 
Oversee stewardship and data lifecycle practices across the agency to ensure data is well managed, high quality, and fit-for-purpose.  
Oversee the AI Impact Assessment process and provide strategic advice on emerging data and technology risks. 
Oversee governance of AUSTRAC’s data sharing arrangements, MOUs and access frameworks to ensure compliance with legislative and policy obligations. 
Represent AUSTRAC in whole-of-government data governance forums and contribute to cross-agency initiatives that require coordinated data management and policy alignment. 
Prepare high-quality briefings, plans and risk assessments for senior executives and governance committees, and support uplift in data literacy and responsible data practices across AUSTRAC. 

For more information about the role and the capabilities where looking for, please refer to the Candidate Pack on the AUSTRAC Careers Page

Affirmative Measures

This vacancy is also being advertised concurrently under both general and affirmative measures recruitment processes.

Applications made under affirmative measures are only available to affirmative measures indigenous applicants or affirmative measures disability applicants.

Evidence will be requested if your application progresses under an affirmative measures process.

Notes

This recruitment process will initially be used to fill a current vacancy and in future, may be used to fill similar positions in the event positions become vacant. The merit pools established from this recruitment process will be valid for 18 months from the date of advertising.

We offer competitive remuneration and great conditions, including:

Annual leave of 4 weeks (20 days) per year + additional paid Christmas close down.

·       Cultural, Ceremonial and NAIDOC leave.

·       18 days of paid personal leave per year.

·       15.4% superannuation, which continues through paid parental leave.

·       18 weeks of paid parental leave.

·       Competitive APS salaries with access to annual salary progression.

·       Study assistance - up to $6,000 per annum and up to 120 hours of study leave.

View the AUSTRAC Enterprise Agreement for more information about current salaries and other conditions of employment.

About Us

AUSTRAC, Australia’s financial intelligence agency and anti-money laundering and terrorism financing regulator, is undergoing a significant transformation to enhance its role in combating money laundering and terrorism financing. This includes proposed expansion of its regulatory regime and a broader digital transformation to support our growing agency. As we embrace these changes and grow, our focus is on fostering innovation, collaboration, and effective problem-solving within an inclusive and supportive work environment. At AUSTRAC, you’ll be part of a team dedicated to maintaining the integrity of Australia’s financial system and making a real impact in preventing financial crime.

Closing Date and further details 

Applications close at 11:30 pm on Sunday 25 January 2026

For enquiries, please contact: Louise 0427 508 769

Please note, we can only accept applications via the AUSTRAC Careers Portal.

Job Title: Director, Multiple Opportunities - Data Governance, Data Strategy and Delivery
Company: Australian Transaction Reports and Analysis Centre (AUSTRAC)
Category:
Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
AUSTRAC is hiring two positions to join the Data Strategy and Collections branch, where our focus is strengthening the agency's enterprise data governance strategy, and maximising the value of our data in achieving regulatory and intelligence priorities This recruitment process will be used to fill current vacancies and build a merit pool for future roles. 

These Director roles offer a unique opportunity to help shape major enterprise shifts and uplift data culture and literacy across AUSTRAC. As a key data leader of the Data Division, your specialist data expertise and oversight across data capability initiatives will cultivate AUSTRAC's data governance strategy and culture. 

Be part of our transformation journey as we evolve into a world leading data-driven, digital agency in financial regulation and intelligence. If you embrace challenges diligently, are passionate about leading teams in a collaborative environment, and are eager to make a meaningful impact we encourage you to apply. 

Director, Data Strategy and Delivery 

You will be responsible for the coordination, alignment and delivery of AUSTRAC's strategic data capability initiatives to support data integrity, continuous enhancement and seamless integration. Your role is critical in ensuring high-quality, consistent data is available within AUSTRAC's regulatory and intelligence functions. You will influence and guide various stakeholders in integrating data outcomes in portfolio projects, while instilling best practice data governance and management principles. As a decisive and people-focussed leader, you will nurture a high-performing team of data professionals to deliver high-quality, operational data capabilities which are critical to support AUSTRAC's regulatory and intelligence operations. 

Key duties include: 

Design, develop and maintain AUSTRAC’s data initiatives and plans to ensure accurate and consistent data is available for AUSTRAC’s regulatory and intelligence functions. 
Product management of strategic data initiatives to align with AUSTRAC’s Reform and Transformation priorities, ensuring effective risk managemnet, governance pracices and sustainability. 
Lead cross-functional teams to design and deliver data plans and other strategic initiatives within cloud-based data integration architectures—including ETL and streaming processes, APIs, and data warehouse systems, and facilitate the democratisation and sharing of data with internal and external partners. 
Collaborate with various stakeholders to elicit business needs and design strategic data solutions that enable their use in analysis, business intelligence, and data science; overseeing the translation of these into data plans, projects, and initiatives. 

Director, Data Governance 

Your focus will be establishing and ensuring adherence to AUSTRAC's data governance frameworks, with the goal of optimising the use and flow of data whilst ensuring our data is safe and secure. Your role will be pivotal in managing controls to drive actionable data for intelligence, regulatory operations, and corporate needs. You will serve as a point of escalation for governance, data quality and protection issues and will work closely with agency leadership to improve the quality and value of core data assets. As a trusted, governance leader, you will build agency-wide understanding of data governance and lead a high-performing team to embed these practices across the agency.  

Key duties include:  

Lead the design, implementation and continuous improvement of AUSTRAC’s enterprise data governance framework, including AI governance and assurance activities, ensuring alignment with whole-of-government requirements and responsible use of AI and automated systems. 
Oversee stewardship and data lifecycle practices across the agency to ensure data is well managed, high quality, and fit-for-purpose.  
Oversee the AI Impact Assessment process and provide strategic advice on emerging data and technology risks. 
Oversee governance of AUSTRAC’s data sharing arrangements, MOUs and access frameworks to ensure compliance with legislative and policy obligations. 
Represent AUSTRAC in whole-of-government data governance forums and contribute to cross-agency initiatives that require coordinated data management and policy alignment. 
Prepare high-quality briefings, plans and risk assessments for senior executives and governance committees, and support uplift in data literacy and responsible data practices across AUSTRAC. 

For more information about the role and the capabilities where looking for, please refer to the Candidate Pack on the AUSTRAC Careers Page

This recruitment process will initially be used to fill a current vacancy and in future, may be used to fill similar positions in the event positions become vacant. The merit pools established from this recruitment process will be valid for 18 months from the date of advertising.

We offer competitive remuneration and great conditions, including:

Annual leave of 4 weeks (20 days) per year + additional paid Christmas close down.

To learn how we exceed expectations to deliver outstanding results, please visit us at www.infosysconsultinginsights.com. Infosys Consulting - the consultancy that truly serves real consultants.

Requirements

We are looking for a Lead Data Scientist to join our team in Sydney. This senior role requires strong business and technical expertise to lead data science initiatives, drive AI/ML solution delivery, and guide a top-performing team using Databricks.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead and mentor a team in AI/ML solution delivery aligned with business goals.
Architect complex workflows and optimize MLOps pipelines on Databricks.
Develop solutions leveraging Large Language Models (LLMs) like Mistral and GPT-4.
Communicate technical concepts to business stakeholders and deliver presentations.
Ensure compliance with regulatory and ethical AI frameworks.

Required Skills:

8+ years in Data Science or AI roles with hands-on Databricks expertise.
Strong knowledge of MLOps and model lifecycle management.
Experience with LLMs and proficiency in Python, SQL, and cloud environments (Azure preferred).
Proven leadership and exceptional communication skills.

Nice to Have:

Experience in banking or regulated industries.
Familiarity with model risk management and responsible AI.
Knowledge of relevant Azure services.

Category:
Database Development & Administration (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
A career at ASIC will broaden and deepen your already accomplished knowledge, skills and abilities. By working on cutting edge issues, you'll make a difference to our goals, Australia's economic reputation and wellbeing and your own career aspirations 

ASIC's Data & Analytics Technology team is seeking an experienced and highly capable Data Modeller to join their high performing team.

 

Sydney or Melbourne locations
24-month fixed term position
Salary from $163,970 to $181,284 (depending on experience) + 15.4 % superannuation
Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Sunday 18 January 2026 

 

The team 

ASIC's Digital, Data & Technology group delivers a broad suite of IT capabilities to support ASIC. We are currently driving major technology initiatives that will accelerate our transformation across key areas including virtualisation, data analytics, mobility, and cloud. The Data & Analytics Technology team underpins these efforts by providing essential services to our primary stakeholder, the Data & Analytics Office. 

 

The role

As a Data Modeller you will be responsible for translating complex business requirements into clear, scalable data models across conceptual, logical and physical layers. These models will underpin analytics, reporting and operational processes. Collaborating closely with data engineers, analysts and business stakeholders the Data Modeller will ensure that data assets are well-structured, standardised and fully aligned with established governance and quality frameworks.

 

More specifically, you will: 

Design and maintain conceptual, logical and physical data models to support development and enhancements across ASIC's data infrastructure, including but not limited to data lakes, application databases, and BI/analytics solutions.
Collaborate effectively with business stakeholders and application/solution teams to define requirements and document data transformations.
Conduct peer reviews of data models developed by team members and external suppliers to ensure quality and consistency.
Take on additional responsibilities and tasks as required, demonstrating flexibility and commitment to team objectives.
Work in a professional, positive and cooperative manner, modelling ASIC's core values of Accountability, Professionalism and Teamwork.

 

About you

The ideal candidate for this role is a data modelling professional who thrives on turning complex business challenges into elegant, scalable solutions. With deep expertise in data modelling tools and strong knowledge of relational and NoSQL technologies, you will bring both technical precision and strategic insight expertise. You will communicate with clarity, collaborate seamlessly across teams, while championing data governance and quality more broadly. Adaptable and values-driven, you will embody ASIC's principles of Accountability, Professionalism and Teamwork while delivering impactful outcomes.

 

In addition, you will have:

Proven ability to quickly interpret complex business requirements and translate them into logical and physical data models using industry-standard modelling tools.
Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, with the capability to convey technical concepts clearly to non-technical audiences.
Extensive hands-on experience with ERwin Data Modeller for designing and maintaining data models.
Strong experience with relational and data warehouse design techniques and modelling methodologies (Kimball, Inmon, Data Vault 2.0, NoSQL).
Familiarity with cloud data platforms and technologies (e.g. AWS, Databricks).
Comprehensive knowledge of established data management principles, frameworks, and technologies.

 

Click ‘apply' to start your application. Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Sunday 18 January 2026.

 

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

ASIC is committed to a providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.

 

We offer a range of employee benefits including:

Attractive superannuation
Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development

 

Click here to view ASIC's salary and benefits guide.

To read more about ASIC, you can visit our website or review our Corporate Plan.

To work with us, you need to be an Australian citizen and be prepared to complete an ASIC Suitability and Baseline Assessment.

Job Title: Financial Analyst – Leasing and Revenue Analytics
Ad Text:
About the Role

This is a high-impact Financial Analyst role with genuine ownership, partnering closely with senior Leasing leaders to drive revenue, portfolio performance, and strategic decision-making across a large retail property portfolio.

What you’ll do:

Partner closely with the Leasing team and respective Regional Leasing Manager, owning the leasing performance of your assigned regions and driving initiatives that maximise revenue and portfolio outcomes.

Lead budgeting and forecasting for your regions, providing accurate assumptions, meaningful analysis, and proactive recommendations, utilising analytical skills, scenario modelling, and reporting tools in Yardi and Power BI to drive better outcomes.

Challenge assumptions, identify risks and opportunities, and provide clear recommendations to support decision-making at Regional and Executive level.

Deliver data-driven insights on key leasing metrics including occupancy, rent spreads, vacancy rates, and leasing performance to inform strategic decisions

Support and contribute to monthly Board and Executive reporting, ensuring insights are clear, commercial, and decision-focused

Take end-to-end ownership of Investor Presentation deliverables, working closely with senior stakeholders to ensure accuracy, narrative clarity, and readiness for external scrutiny

Drive budgeting and forecasting of third line revenue, including Media, ATM, Vending Machine, CML, and Vacant Shop Income, ensuring robust assumptions and reporting.

Drive continuous improvement through better utilisation of Yardi and Power BI, enhancing the efficiency, automation, and impact of reporting and analysis.

About You

2–4 years’ experience in financial or management reporting, ideally in Retail Property, but open to other asset classes.

Comfortable operating in a fast-paced, senior stakeholder environment, with the confidence to challenge constructively and influence outcomes.

Strong experience as a Finance Business Partner, ideally supporting Leasing and/or Property Operations teams to deliver commercial insights and performance improvements.

Proven background in Financial Analysis, with hands-on experience in budgeting, forecasting, and variance analysis.

Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills, with the ability to influence and present insights to senior leaders.

Experience working with large, complex data sets, translating detail into clear commercial insights.

CA/CPA qualified


Good to Have

Solid understanding of leasing performance metrics, including occupancy, rent spreads, vacancy rates, and leasing outcomes.

Experience contributing to Investor Presentations, Q&A materials, and verification reports, ensuring high-quality and accurate outputs.

Demonstrated ability to drive process improvements and automation through enhanced system utilisation and data-led analytics.

Advanced skills in Excel and Power BI — building dashboards, Scenario Models, and delivering actionable insights for senior stakeholders.


Note: We are not accepting applications from recruitment agencies for this role.

Optus is an Australian telecommunications company, delivering more than 11 million services to our customers every day across mobile, broadband, and digital solutions.

The Senior Business Analyst - CIAM will play a key role in shaping how Optus onboards, identifies, and authenticates customers across all channels. Sitting within the CIAM program and reporting to the Director, this role partners closely with specialists across identity verification, authentication, and customer data to translate complex business needs into clear requirements. You'll help turn regulations, policies, and strategic objectives into actionable project outcomes, ensuring strong controls, smarter processes, and a seamless, secure customer identity experience.

In this high‑impact position, you'll drive priority initiatives such as building end‑to‑end identity reporting to detect issues and strengthen compliance, as well as defining requirements for unified authentication and new centralised identity verification services. Drawing on strong analytical and technical skills, you'll provide insights that drive real improvement and support fraud prevention, customer protection, and operational excellence. This role offers broad exposure across Senior Management, Risk, Finance, Sales, Service, Product, Engineering, Customer Insights, and Marketing.

What you'll be doing

Lead multiple CIAM projects, ensuring requirements are well‑defined and aligned to business and customer needs.
Act as a key liaison between CIAM, IT, senior leadership, SMEs, and experience teams to design compliant and improved identity and authentication solutions.
Maintain up‑to‑date expertise in large‑scale customer identity verification and authentication, including industry trends and emerging practices.
Produce high‑quality analysis and documentation for high‑risk projects, including business requirements, use cases, scope matrices, future‑state designs, and UAT plans.
Oversee project governance by identifying identity‑related risks and compliance issues across initiatives.
Manage and maintain the CIAM risk register, ensuring risks are actively tracked, escalated when required, and visible to senior stakeholders.

What makes you perfect for the role?

Degree in business, computer science, or a related field.
5+ years' analytics expertise across data integration, visualisation, SQL, and large datasets.
Identity, authentication & risk knowledge, including credit risk and compliance reporting.
Strong project and stakeholder skills, with proficiency in MS Project, Visio, Excel, BI tools, and clear communication.
Excellent analytical, presentation, and problem‑solving skills, with strong interpersonal and influencing capability.

Optus is a place where we let you do you. We offer a range of benefits including:

Competitive remuneration and employee discounts. Make life easier (and more affordable) with $80 monthly credit and 25% off Optus products and unique shopping discounts with our retail partners.
Flexible working arrangements with opportunities to work three days in the office, two days remote or home.
Vibrant and collaborative office campus that includes cafes, convenience store, chill out zones, GP, post office, gym and on-site childcare centre.
Competitive leave policies, including additional 'Connected' days to focus on culture, family, health, community, or whatever's important to you.
We support growing families with inclusive, carer-neutral paid Parental Leave of up to 16 weeks.
Direct your own development and build future-ready skills with Optus U's industry-focused micro-credentials, developed with La Trobe and Macquarie Universities.
Build meaningful connections through employee-led networks and diversity initiatives including Culture Connect, Elevate Women, Disability Network and Express Yourself (LGBTQIA+).
Put your wellbeing first with free access to counselling and support services, 24/7 — in-person, by phone, SMS, or video.

We are seeking a currently seeking a Guidewire ClaimCenter Business Analyst to join our team. Harvey Norman’s Information Technology Department’s core focus is to deliver innovative IT solutions by delivering crucial projects to achieve the strategic goals of the business.

We have recently embarked on a journey to streamline processes, reduce technological complexity, and boost efficiency within our people management systems. This initiative will improve people data management, compliance, visibility and analytics, productivity, and employee engagement for approximately 15,000 people across Australia and New Zealand.

About the role  

This is a fantastic opportunity to be part of a large scale, complex HCM transformation. Joining a multi-disciplinary agile team, working closely with Technology, WFM/Payroll and HR leads, you will be responsible for leading business requirements & process analysis, and developing & executing test scenarios, focusing on Dayforce Implementation on downstream systems. 

This is Full Time Maximum Term Contract for up to 12 months, with an ideal commencement date in the first week of February 2026.

You will;

Requirements Gathering: Assist the WFM/Payroll & HR lead and collaborate with stakeholders to review, gather, document, and prioritise business requirements related to Dayforce implementation impacts of any downstream systems.
Business Process Analysis: Assist the WFM/Payroll lead, HR lead and Technology SME’s in analysing existing and future state business processes of downstream systems, identify areas for improvement in alignment with Dayforce capabilities, project team and SI partner. Facilitate stakeholder meetings to drive requirements, consider alternatives and negotiate project outcomes within milestone timeframes.
Testing: Work closely with both the Dayforce and Technology leads to assist & execute SIT/End-to-End testing, including documenting integration & downstream system test scenarios, validating errors or adjustments to user stories/acceptance criteria test scripts.
Detailed Procedure Documentation: Work closely with internal Payroll, WFM, technology SME’s, project leads and SI partner functional consultants to contribute to & review detailed administrator procedures for using Technology related administration related to the Integration services and all downstream systems
Team Support and Collaboration: Foster cross-team collaboration to help project team members complete project tasks and produce deliverables. Participate in your team's operating rhythm and provide progress updates through agreed forums and channels.

About you  

You will have extensive experience as a Senior Business Analyst in a similar role, with a proven track record of successfully delivering large complex IT projects. You will bring strong analytical thinking and problem-solving skills, enabling you to lead workshops, guide discussions, and provide insightful analysis for your projects. You’ll also have a keen ability to identify opportunities for improvement and drive meaningful change.

You will also have: 

Experience working on HR/Payroll/WFM projects across any ERP
Experience in writing business and project documentation to support the implementation of technology solutions.
Excellent written and verbal communication, with the ability to effectively communicate with business stakeholders.
Knowledge of project management lifecycles and product implementation methodologies (waterfall, agile, hybrid).
Proficiency in asking insightful questions to uncover the underlying reasons behind stakeholder processes.
Strong ability to manage multiple initiatives simultaneously and prioritise competing deadlines.
Expertise in the management and execution of end-to-end system testing
Ability to partner effectively with the business to ensure outcomes align with business needs and objectives.
Tertiary qualifications in IT, Business or Engineering.

This opportunity will provide: 

Access to Udemy, an online training platform with over 5,500 courses.
Experience working with an Iconic Australian Brand with global success in NZ, Asia, and Europe.
A supportive team environment that celebrates diversity and promotes a healthy work and family life balance. 
Opportunities to make discounted purchases on a great range of products and services.

Have we got your interest?  

Apply now to be considered to join our dedicated team.  

Please note that only people with the right to work in Australia should apply for this position.  

Recruitment Agencies – thank you for thinking of us, however we do endeavour to fill our opportunities through direct channels wherever possible. If we find that we do need agency assistance, we’ll be in touch.

Job Title: Senior Manager - Finance Systems and Reporting
Ad Text:
Take hold of a monster opportunity and join our Finance and Tax team as a Senior Manager - Finance Systems and Reporting. If you’re a good fit for this role and live in Brisbane, Sydney or Melbourne we’d love you to apply. 




Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

As the Senior Manager - Finance Systems and Reporting, you will oversee the development, maintenance, management, and implementation of Finance and Tax technology, data strategies, roadmaps, automation reporting, and continuous improvement initiatives. You will drive alignment and improvement for all Finance and Tax platforms/systems, services and vendors ensuring they effectively enable the delivery of financial data and regulatory reporting.

Key aspects of the role include:

Finance Technology & Systems Management

Manage financial technology platforms and integrate with enterprise systems.
Collaborate with IT and Finance teams to enhance system functionality and ensure compliance with regulations.
Oversee configuration, development, vendor relationships, and continuous improvements.
Risk management and governance oversight, including 1st line risk responsibility.
Change management and system testing.

Data Management, Reporting & Analytics

Implement data strategies, ensuring accuracy and accessibility.
Lead data governance including the use of Power BI tools for reporting.
Compile ESG and climate data.
Improve data quality and automation in financial processes.
Ensure compliance with regulatory reporting.

AI & Automation in Finance

Identify and implement AI-driven financial forecasting and automation.
Develop AI models for risk assessments and financial optimisation.
Drive process automation in finance operations.

Stakeholder Collaboration & Leadership

Align technology strategies between finance, IT, and business leadership.
Ensure financial systems support business goals.

Innovation & Continuous Improvement

Recommend and implement emerging technology solutions.
Drive digital transformation initiatives.

Leadership

Manage a high-performing team and foster a strong team culture.
Maintain relationships with enablement teams and vendors.

This role is available as 12-month max-term/ secondment opportunity. This role is known internally as Senior Manager - Finance and Tax, Systems and Reporting.

About you

It goes without saying you'll be a great communicator with top notch interpersonal skills. We'll also expect you to pick up problems and come up with quick, creative ways to solve them. It's quite likely you tick some of the following boxes too:  

Financial Systems and Data Skills.
AI knowledge.
Relevant superannuation business experience, regulatory reporting, tax and accounting experience.
Project Management and agile software implementation.
Excellent problem solving, analytical and process development/improvement skills.
The ability to think strategically with a commercial focus and respond to emerging issues and develop appropriate strategies and plans.
Demonstrated experience leading and developing a high performing team.

About us

Our 2.3 million members trust us to take care of almost $330 billion in retirement savings. And we help them take charge of their finances and face the future with confidence. Our inclusive culture means you’ll be valued and heard in a respectful workplace. We've created an environment where you can be yourself and do amazing work. It's that simple.

Apply online now

Everyone is welcome to apply. We value diverse thinking, cultures, perspectives, backgrounds, and abilities. Awaken your career at Australian Retirement Trust and apply now. Applications close Sunday, 25 January 2025.

We don’t want to leave you with a monstrous wait. So, you’ll hear from us after the closing date to find out whether you’ve made it through to the next round or not. Being fair and up-front is important to us – and recruitment is no different.

Principal BI Solution Architect, Ongoing opportunity based in Sydney CBD + hybrid/flexible working options available

Ongoing, full-time opportunity
Clerk grade:11/12
Salary range: $149,739 - $173,174 p.a. plus superannuation and leave loading
Location: Sydney

Help solve the State's most challenging problems with data and analytics.
What drives State decisions around housing? What determines safety standards across our workplaces? And how does the State decide the best allocation of resources and funding?

The most challenging Government problems are solved using analytics. The best outcomes for NSW citizens are driven by reliable data and insights, developed by highly skilled and motivated analytics teams. This is your opportunity to join one of them.

If you're passionate about transforming data into actionable insights that shape policy, improve public services, and drive smarter decision-making, join the Department of Customer Service as a Principal BI Solution Architect - where your expertise will directly impact critical government initiatives.

You'll be joining a motivated and high-performing analytics team who:

Have a defined remit to develop and deliver high-value analytics use cases for DCS and its leaders
Are trusted advisors to the executive leadership team, with proven strategic and analytical expertise and a track record of delivering impactful budget, people and regulatory outcomes for the Department
Have an established reputation, strong executive presence and play a key role in influencing business decisions and direction through analytics
Own, maintain and develop several critical reporting solutions for the Department and its external partner agencies
Strive to create value and drive business outcomes through every data point, insight and solution we produce

Your responsibilities will be to:

Engage and collaborate with business and technical stakeholders to define requirements and propose solutions that meet business and customer needs and align with business and technology strategy
Lead the design, implementation and testing of technology solutions and report on delivery commitments to ensure solutions are implemented as expected and to agreed timeframes
Establish, build and maintain stakeholder relationships through effective, communication, negotiation and issues management to ensure stakeholders are engaged effectively throughout project ideation and delivery
Take technical ownership of solutions to ensure that business needs are met, support contracts are being satisfactorily delivered and procurement activities and negotiation with suppliers are competitive
Provide expert advice and technical input into technology strategy and architecture for Agency enterprise, and critical communications operational support systems and business support systems, in order to meet business and customer needs and maximise return on technology investment
Maintain knowledge and expertise in relevant technology, practices and industry trends in order to recommend and deliver innovative solutions in line with organisational and government prioritie.

We'd love to hear from you if you…

Have demonstrated, real-work experience in delivering complex BI solutions, data visualisation, data science or advanced analytics.
Have experience with designing, developing and deploying reporting solutions in Power BI, Tableau, QLIK or similar while ensuring performance, interpretability, and explainability.
Have deep understanding of best practices in analytics, data governance, and data reporting applications.
Have experience working in cross-functional teams, including data engineers, analysts, and business leaders.
Have experience guiding, supporting, coaching or mentoring junior team members and reviewing deliverables.
Are experienced in data storytelling and presenting analytical insights in a compelling and impactful way.
Can distil complex technical challenges into simple, achievable solutions and milestones.
Approach every challenge with an open and solution-orientated mindset.
Have tertiary qualifications in Statistics, Mathematics, Data Science, Computer Science, Information Technology, Econometrics or a related field.

…and can demonstrate the following technical skills and qualifications:

Advanced familiarity with Microsoft Fabric and cloud-based data platforms, preferably certified in DP-600 (Microsoft Certified: Fabric Analytics Engineer Associate) and/or DP-700 (Microsoft Certified: Fabric Data Engineer Associate)
Advanced expertise in Power BI for data visualisation and reporting.
Advanced expertise in SQL (advanced queries, performance tuning and functions).
Intermediate expertise in Tableau and/or QLIK for data visualisation and reporting.
Excellent understanding of data modelling and data visualisation principles.
Familiarity with SAP Business Warehouse (SAP BW) and working with SAP data structures.
Familiarity with version control and CI/CD pipelines for data workflows.
Strong grasp of data governance, data quality, and security best practices.

How to Apply

Please click on the Apply Now button and attach your resume (max 2 pages) and cover letter (max 1 page). Ensure that both highlight your skills and suitability for this role, as outlined against the requirements above.

A talent pool may be created to fill future ongoing or temporary opportunities.

Salary Grade 11/12, with the base salary for this role starting at $149,739 base plus superannuation

At GMHBA, every day is a chance to make a real impact on people's lives. Join our people-focused, not-for-profit health insurer and enjoy a flexible workplace, supportive culture, and a rewarding regional lifestyle. For 90 years, we've put our members, and our people, first. Make your career meaningful with GMHBA.



About the opportunity
GMHBA is on a data-driven journey to enhance business intelligence and analytics across the organisation. As a Data Engineer / Data Warehouse Developer, you will design, build, and maintain scalable data solutions that transform raw information into actionable insights. You'll work with Azure cloud environments, manage complex data feeds, and ensure data integrity and quality, while partnering with stakeholders to deliver timely reporting and analytics that drive decision-making. This role offers the chance to contribute to meaningful business change, support compliance and audit processes, and strengthen GMHBA's data capabilities across the organisation.



This is a full time, 6 month fixed term contract. We offer hybrid working with the option to work from home 3 days per week.

The ideal candidate:

5+ years' experience in SQL development and data engineering roles, with tertiary qualifications in Computer Science or a related field (or equivalent experience).


Experience with Azure Synapse, Azure Data Factory, Azure Data Lake Storage, and Azure SQL Managed Instance/DB.


Hands-on experience with ETL/ELT pipelines, warehouse automation, data modelling (Kimball, Dimensional, Relational), and SQL-based solutions including stored procedures and analytical data marts.


Strong understanding of data governance, integrity, quality, and advanced techniques such as CDC, watermarking, and SCD.


Experience providing technical advice to stakeholders, supporting regulatory compliance, reporting, and contributing to business change initiatives.

At GMHBA, we are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone feels respected, valued, and empowered to be their authentic selves. We believe that inclusion strengthens our organisation, enriches our culture, and allows us to better support our members, patients, and communities. About Us:




We work with our clients to help solve the next generation of public policy challenges

Verian is a world leading, purpose-led and independent research, evidence, evaluation, and communications agency, providing services to government and the public realm. With offices across the globe, our specialist consultants and researchers are supported by our unique global data ecosystem. We provide gold standard data on the economy and society to decision makers.

We combine expertise in human understanding with advanced technologies and data science, connecting governments with citizens across the world. We support the rapid development of policy thinking in moments of urgency. We implement policies on the ground for multi-laterals. We build communications to reach diverse and complex audiences.

We are Verian. Powering decisions that shape the world.




About the role:

As an Associate Director of Evaluation, you'll independently lead large-scale, complex research projects including client management, design of all materials, reporting and presentation. You'll be the strategic partner our clients rely on, designing innovative methodologies, uncovering powerful insights, and presenting recommendations that drive real business impact.




Key Responsibilities:


Drive business growth

Lead complex proposals with compelling methodologies and unique value propositions

Develop strategic growth plans for your area of expertise

Identify and activate new business opportunities

Build and nurture lasting client relationships


Lead & Deliver Excellence

Independently manage major projects from design through to presentation

Create engaging narratives that transform data into actionable insights

Solve complex challenges with creative, evidence-based approaches

Present confidently to clients, executives and key stakeholders


Build Our Brand & Team

Champion thought leadership in your specialist area

Mentor and develop junior talent

Contribute to Verian's national and global growth initiatives

Share expertise across our collaborative network




What You’ll Bring:

10+ years' experience in research and consulting

Deep expertise in both qualitative and quantitative methodologies

Proven track record of managing complex client relationships

Strong commercial acumen with ability to deliver profitable outcomes

Exceptional storytelling and presentation skills

Natural leadership qualities that inspire teams




Why Join Us:

The chance to work on high-impact, meaningful projects that drive real-world change

A competitive salary and benefits package

Learning and development opportunities to help you grow professionally

Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Position Overview

The Project/Program Analyst is part of the Program Management Office (PMO) and plays a key role in supporting governance, reporting, and delivery of digital research infrastructure projects. The role contributes to PMO standards, portfolio reporting, and project assurance while coordinating project activities, supporting procurement and contract management, analysing data, and engaging stakeholders to ensure successful delivery of eResearch initiatives aligned with national and organisational priorities.

The position requires sound judgement, strong analytical skills, and the ability to work independently under limited direction.

Key Responsibilities


Support the planning, coordination, and delivery of eResearch projects and programs, including research data platforms, high-performance computing, and digital research tools.
Monitor project performance, track milestones, and manage risks and issues using appropriate tools and frameworks.
Analyse project data and prepare reports, dashboards, and briefings for internal and external stakeholders.
Maintain accurate and up-to-date project documentation, including schedules, risk registers, and governance records.
Assist in the preparation of business cases, funding submissions, and post-project evaluations.
Coordinate stakeholder engagement activities, including meetings, workshops, and communications.
Ensure compliance with APS policies, procurement rules, and funding agreements.
Lead or support procurement and contract management activities in line with Australian Government frameworks and PMO standards.
Support PMO governance processes, including gate reviews and compliance with portfolio standards.
Contribute to PMO reporting, dashboards, and performance metrics for senior leadership.
Assist in continuous improvement of PMO frameworks, tools, and templates.

Essential Skills & Experience


Demonstrated experience in project or program support, preferably in a research, ICT, or government context.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to interpret complex data and provide insights.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, including the ability to prepare reports and briefings for senior stakeholders.
Proficiency in project management tools and Microsoft Office applications.
Ability to work independently, manage competing priorities, and exercise sound judgement.
Experience supporting procurement and contract management processes within a project or program environment.
Understanding of Australian Government procurement frameworks, policies, and processes.

Highly Desirable Skills


Experience or familiarity with Defence procurement and contract management practices.
Experience with ICTPA Panel procurement processes.

Desirable


Knowledge of eResearch, research data management, or digital research infrastructure.
Familiarity with national research infrastructure initiatives (e.g., ARDC, AARNet, NCRIS).

Job Title: Senior Lecturer in Business Information Systems
Ad Text:
Classification: Academic Level C
Salary package: $146,007 - $162,281 per annum plus 17% superannuation 

Terms: Full time, Continuing

Position Description and Selection Criteria: PD & PEWER Level C Senior Lecturer in Business Information Systems.pdf



Position overview 

The Research School of Management in the ANU College of Business and Economics aims to create and share management knowledge that makes a difference to organisations and society. Nine academics with affiliations to our School are listed among the 2025 Stanford/Elsevier Top 2% Scientists.

To continue the current growth trajectory, we are seeking to recruit a Senior Lecturer (Level C) in the field of Business Information Systems. The successful applicant will conduct research of international standing and actively contribute to undergraduate and postgraduate teaching in the School. They will have a strong work ethic, a practical approach, and be passionate about the quality of their work. The successful applicant will join a strong team of academics who publish in top international journals and hold external competitive grants. The School and College provide an excellent research environment, including favourable teaching load and internal research support. 

The position is open to international applicants. The successful applicant must be available to commence work in Canberra, Australia by mid-2026. The successful applicant will be offered relocation assistance as per ANU Policy.

We have a strong equal opportunity culture. We encourage all applicants particularly, female, Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander applicants. 

For further information, please contact Associate Professor Ashkan Zarghami, E: ashkan.zarghami@anu.edu.au

College overview 

The Australian National University (ANU) is one of the world’s great universities, ranking 32nd in the 2026 QS World University Rankings. The Research School of Management sits within the ANU College of Business and Economics. The College educates the next generation of business leaders, professional economists and academics. Our graduates have the knowledge and skills to lead organisations, design public policy, and research the big issues of business and economy.

Located in the national capital, we engage deeply with the business and policy communities. Our academics lead public debate on the critical issues of our time through their research, which is both long term and strategic in focus. Our internationally diverse student body is evenly divided between undergraduate and postgraduate study, and we have a large doctoral program. Our alumni are found in the world's leading companies, policy agencies and universities. 

We strongly believe that the way in which we operate is defined by our Values and Behaviours and encourage you to apply if you are looking for a workplace that encourages respect, collegiality and excellence. 

The University actively encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people. For more information on employment opportunities, contact our Indigenous Employment Consultant on indigenous.employment@anu.edu.au.

ANU values diversity and inclusion and believes employment opportunities must not be limited by socio-economic background, race, religion or gender. For more information about staff equity at ANU, visit https://services.anu.edu.au/business-units/human-resources-division/equity-and-diversity 

Application information

In order to apply for this role please make sure that you upload the following documents:

A statement (3 pages max) addressing the selection criteria.
A current curriculum vitae (CV) which includes the names and contact details of at least three referees (preferably including a current or previous supervisor). If your CV does not include referees you can complete these online when prompted in the application form.
Other documents, if required.

Applications which do not address the selection criteria may not be considered for the position.

Please note: The successful candidate will be required to undergo a background check during the recruitment process.  An offer of employment is conditional on satisfactory results.

 Closing date: Thursday, 15 January 2026, 11.55 (Canberra Time)
